  "market_context": "Late June to early July 2023 daily price action on DXY, following a peak around June 29, with a subsequent downward move. Analyst evaluates bias using PD array respect, failure to displace below previous day low, and swing point structure.",
  "key_observation": "Price repeatedly failed to close outside the prior day’s range and respected a PD array (fair value gap), indicating continuation bias until draw on liquidity (sell-side liquidity at swing low) was reached.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a fair value gap (PD array) below current price and noted price drawing toward it.",
    "Step 2: Observed price could not displace below the previous day low, leading analyst to anticipate a move toward previous day high instead.",
    "Step 3: Noted price reached up but failed to close outside the prior day’s range, reinforcing expectation of lower move toward sell-side liquidity above a fair value gap.",
    "Step 4: After price moved down into the drawn liquidity (FVG), analyst confirmed closure back inside the range, signaling potential reversal or consolidation.",
    "Step 5: Applied Next Day Model: with PD array respected, anticipated next candle would be bullish (open-low-high-close) targeting either previous day high or a marked swing high.",
    "Step 6: When price closed outside a swing high but failed to sustain, analyst shifted focus to lower targets—previous day low or deeper swing points—as draw on liquidity remained unmet.",
    "Step 7: Reviewed left-side structure to identify stacked swing lows as alternative liquidity targets when immediate levels were not swept."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Maintain directional bias as long as price respects PD arrays and fails to displace key structure; only shift bias after liquidity is drawn and closure confirms change in state. Next Day Model provides high-probability anticipation when structure holds.",
